      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IT'S A TEASE (3) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 4.5 lengths at this track in a handy 29.74 beating FASCINATE MARIA. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Can continue on her winning ways. ZIPPING GRESSIER (1) goes very well here starting 10 times for four wins and two minors. Below best last time at this track (30.12) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 5.5 lengths fourth. Looks a key chance on best figures. MY MONROE (8) produced a moderate performance last time when seventh at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Hard Style Girl (30.45) in a Grade 4/5. Has ability and can atone. PITMAN GO QUICK (2) can fill a top-three spot.",
